news.title: IIT Indore making 'smart glass' to keep buildings cool in summer and warm in winter
news.para: Indian Institute of Technology Indore is developing a smart glass. This glass uses a special polymer. It can control light and heat using electricity. This technology will help construct eco-friendly buildings. The smart glass changes color quickly. It saves energy by reducing the need for cooling and lighting. Researchers are working with industry partners to produce this glass.

news.title: Aldar Properties posts 24% rise in profit in H1 2025
news.para: Aldar Properties, Abu Dhabi's top developer, saw a profit increase. This rise is due to strong project backlogs and high international interest. Chinese buyers are leading this demand. Sales to Chinese investors have already surpassed last year's total. International buyers now make up a large portion of Aldar's UAE sales. The company will focus on domestic operations in the Emirates.

news.title: Asian Paints net profit dips 5.88% in Q1 FY26
news.para: Asian Paints reported a 5.88% dip in net consolidated profit for Q1 FY26, reaching ₹1,117.05 crore. While domestic decorative paints saw a volume growth of 3.9%, revenue declined by 1.2%. International business performed strongly with 11.1% revenue growth, and the company acquired the remaining stake in White Teak, making it a wholly-owned subsidiary.

news.title: Kolte-Patil Developers posts net loss of ₹16.88 crore in Q1 FY26
news.para: Kolte-Patil Developers reported a net consolidated loss after tax of ₹16.88 crore for the quarter ended June 30, 2025, a significant downturn from the ₹6.37 crore profit in the same period last year. The company's net consolidated total income also decreased substantially by 72.37% to ₹96.81 crore in Q1 FY26.

news.title: After 23 years, Prayagraj civic body to prepare new ‘khasra’ of buildings
news.para: Prayagraj is set for a major property record update. The Prayagraj Municipal Corporation will create a new 'Khasra' for all buildings. This initiative aims to address house tax discrepancies. A door-to-door survey will gather building details. The new 'Khasra' preparation is scheduled to begin in January 2026. This will update property records and boost corporation income.

news.title: Tenders invited for phase 1 of Vijayawada metro
news.para: The AP Metro Rail Corporation Limited has initiated e-tenders for the first phase of the Vijayawada metro project, a 38.4 km stretch estimated at ₹4,150 crore. This includes a 4.33 km double-decker flyover and one underground station, along with 32 elevated stations across two corridors. Bidding opens August 4, with a pre-bid meeting scheduled for August 18.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh government issues LRS guidelines, extends cut-off to June 30
news.para: The Andhra Pradesh government is set to resolve pending Layout Regularisation Scheme (LRS) applications, benefiting plot owners in unauthorized layouts across the state. The decision follows the cabinet's approval and extends the cut-off date to June 30, 2025, to accommodate previously unregistered plots.

news.title: New guidelines for house numbers, repair permissions in Goa
news.para: The urban development department in Panaji has introduced new guidelines. These guidelines streamline the process for issuing separate house numbers. This helps nuclear families get independent utility connections. Municipal councils can now grant repair permissions for legally registered structures.

news.title: In two years, Ahmedabad's 14,907 units in 1,151 buildings declared dangerous
news.para: Ahmedabad faces escalating risks of structural collapses during the monsoon, highlighted by recent incidents in Payal Flats and Suryasagar Apartments. The AMC has identified thousands of unsafe units, yet enforcement of safety regulations remains weak. Despite past tragedies and mandated structural stability certificates, compliance is lacking, exacerbated by legal and logistical hurdles.

news.title: Online tenant registrations in Pune hit as seven new police stations missing from portal
news.para: Pune residents in rapidly growing areas face challenges registering tenancy agreements online due to seven new police stations not being integrated into the e-registration portal. This discrepancy leads to incorrect police station mapping, causing confusion and potential legal risks for landlords and tenants.

news.title: LuLu Group allotted land in Visakhapatnam and Vijayawada
news.para: The Andhra Pradesh government has allocated land to LuLu Group for mega malls in Vijayawada and Visakhapatnam. APIIC facilitated the 99-year lease. Laurus Labs received 532 acres for a pharma park, investing Rs 5,630 crore and creating jobs. LuLu's Visakhapatnam project, initially cancelled, is revived on the same land. Vijayawada's mall will be built on APSRTC land, facing opposition.

news.title: Over 3.7 lakh properties in Bengaluru yet to pay tax
news.para: BBMP has identified 3.7 lakh properties with Rs 700-800 crore in pending property taxes and will reissue notices via SMS and email. Due to low compliance despite auction notices, BBMP plans to block e-khata accounts of defaulters, preventing property sales until dues are cleared. The process is expected to take 4-5 months.

news.title: Bombay HC orders probe into over 900 redevelopment notices by Mhada for cessed buildings
news.para: The Bombay High Court has strongly criticized Mhada for its executive engineers' misuse of power in issuing over 900 redevelopment notices for cessed buildings, deeming them dangerous without proper jurisdiction. The court highlighted the arbitrariness and illegality of these actions, potentially driven by vested interests exploiting redevelopment incentives.

news.title: Panasonic in talks to buy controlling stake in Focus Lighting and Fixtures
news.para: Panasonic may acquire a controlling stake in Focus Lighting and Fixtures. This would be Panasonic's second electricals acquisition in India. The deal involves buying the Sheth family's shares and a public offer. Negotiations are advanced, but due diligence has revealed issues. The acquisition could cost Panasonic ₹526 crore.

news.title: Unauthorised commercial spaces on residential areas choke streets, roads in Coimbatore
news.para: Coimbatore residents are facing parking chaos due to unauthorized conversion of residential buildings into commercial spaces, particularly in areas like Saibaba Colony. Violators disregard parking regulations, disrupting residential peace. The city corporation has started collecting details to impose fines. Residents are suffering from issues like kitchen fumes and increased health problems.

news.title: Will bring in scheme to provide housing for homeless: Goa CM
news.para: Goa government plans a new housing scheme for the homeless. Pramod Sawant announced it will be similar to the Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojana. Two land patches in Pernem are identified for 1BHK flats. A 30-year residency is required. MLAs want a clear definition of 'homeless' and a survey. They also want a contractor to build houses.

news.title: MahaRERA lists 1,244 projects ‘under abeyance’ in Pune district
news.para: Thousands of homebuyers in Maharashtra, particularly in Pune, are facing uncertainty as 1,244 projects are marked 'under abeyance' by MahaRERA due to lack of completion certificates or extension applications. Many individuals' investments are stuck, with some waiting over a decade for possession.

news.title: SC okays redevelopment of Mumbai's Motilal Nagar under C&DA model
news.para: The Supreme Court has greenlit the redevelopment of Mumbai's Motilal Nagar under MHADA's C&DA model, dismissing challenges from residents' associations. The project, executed with Adani Realty's Estatevue, will rehouse 3,700 residents in modern 1,600 sq ft apartments, a significant upgrade from their existing 230 sq ft homes.

news.title: Mumbai police files chargesheet against Sai Estate Consultants in ₹11 crore fraud case
news.para: Mumbai police have filed a chargesheet against Amit and Vicky Wadhwani of Sai Estate Consultants for allegedly cheating MAD (India) Pvt Ltd out of over Rs 11 crore. The advertising agency claims the Wadhwanis failed to pay for services rendered between 2017 and 2024.

news.title: Indore cops register FIR in land registry 'scam' estimated to be worth ₹100 crore
news.para: Indore police have registered a case regarding a land registry scam potentially worth ₹100 crore. The investigation was initiated after discrepancies were found in the registration department's record room, including mismatched buyer/seller details and missing fingerprints on documents.
